						               													<description>You are one of &amp;ldquo;Crust&amp;rdquo; &amp;ndash; the neighborhood pizzeria delivery drivers.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The Pizzeria owner knows that a good pizza delivery is when the pizza arrive to the customer Fast and Hot.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;That will make the customer happy and a loyal one.&amp;#10;How can the pizzeria owner know the pizza was served fast and hot?&amp;#10;By the tips the delivery Driver gets from the customers.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;That&amp;rsquo;s why at the end of each day the pizzeria owner checks which delivery driver got the most tips and he give him a bonus and the title &amp;ldquo;Employee of the day&amp;rdquo;.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Your mission is to earn the most tips at the end of the day and become &amp;ldquo;employee of the day&amp;rdquo;.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;How to play the game:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;ROUND SETUP&amp;#10;The player picks up a delivery card showing the delivery destination. &amp;#10;The player calculates which the fastest route is for him.&amp;#10;The player throws the dice and advances the number steps indicated by the dice.&amp;#10;The player moves by one count the &amp;quot;pizza marker&amp;quot; that indicates the progress of the delivery.&amp;#10;Each &amp;quot;traffic line&amp;quot; on the road and each &amp;ldquo;road sign&amp;quot; are progress steps included in the play.&amp;#10;Traffic is only allowed in the direction indicated by the arrows on the road signs.&amp;#10;After this, the next player draws a card and repeats the steps.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;PIZZA DELIVERY&amp;#10;Arrival at the delivery destination is considered done when a player threw the dice and moved according to the number on the dice to one of the &amp;ldquo;traffic lines &amp;quot; located across the entrance (address number) of the same house and between the two road signs on its sides.&amp;#10; After a player has arrived to the house and delivered the pizza he will receive a &amp;quot;tip&amp;quot; in money bills, which depends on how fast he has brought the pizza to the customers. The calculation will be based on the number on which the &amp;quot;pizza marker&amp;quot; is located, that counts of the number of turns that the player played until he arrived to the house.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;When the player arrives back to the pizzeria, he picks up another delivery card and repeats the action.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
